&(t,f)
AND of true and false evaluates to false.


|(f,!(f))
NOT of false evaluates to true;
OR of false and true evaluates to true.


!(&(t,t,f))
AND of true, true, and false evaluates to false;
NOT of false evaluates to true.


|(&(t,t),!(f),f)
AND of true and true evaluates to true;
NOT of false evaluates to true;
OR of true, true, and false evaluates to true.

